component.name: DjangoConsoleOptions

option.name: myCustomStartScript

task.summary:
Added an about page and a title to the index page
The about page was added by adding about.html and modifying the views.py, urls.py files. The about page uses a simpler function call in the view rather than by class as were the other examples. Adding the page title by variable to the index was more complicated than expected. I ended up modifying the "context" of the view in order to add the page_title variable, which was then referenceable in the index.html file.

Added a unittest to check page title in the functional_tests.py file
This is a selenium based unittest that loads a chrome browser with a given url localhost:8000/polls and checks the title of the web page that loads. Have been unable to resolve a 503 error that occurs whenever browser.quit() is called. Not sure if this is a legit error in this case as it is not running a selenium grid.
Add lists app to the project and added an initial unit test
Added URL mapping that handles the polls and lists apps

Made lists its own Django app in site settings, updates urls and views
Now the mysite project has two applications: polls and lists. This had to be declared in the site settings.py for the templates path to be seen by the framework. urls and views were updated to flesh out lists to have a index.html and root mapping.
